The paper discusses the problem of signal recovery from underdetermined measurements, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The use of prior information in maximum-a-posteriori estimation is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also employs the replica method, which is a technique commonly used in statistical physics (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of weighted zero-norm minimization, which is a numerical optimization technique relevant to numerical analysis (cs.NA).
